## Investigation Report: PhoneHub Current State Analysis

### Objective
Deep analysis of the current state of the Astro-based PhoneHub site across 10 key areas: brand data, products, pages (brands/search/homepage), news fetching, CI/CD, content agent, components, and Smartprix reference features.

---

### 1. Brand Data Structure

**File**: `c:\Users\96650\OneDrive\Desktop\AI_BA_WORKSPACE\data\brands.json` (single-line JSON, 183 entries)

**Brand fields** (every brand has the same 5 fields):
- `id` (slug string)
- `name` (display name)
- `logo` (URL to Brandfetch CDN or Simple Icons CDN)
- `color` (hex brand color)
- `category` (string: Premium, Value, Budget, Mid-Range, Gaming, Auto, Other)

**Category distribution (brands.json)**:

| Category | Count |
|----------|-------|
| Auto | 128 |
| Other | 22 |
| Value | 17 |
| Premium | 7 |
| Budget | 5 |
| Mid-Range | 3 |
| Gaming | 1 |
| **Total** | **183** |

**Brands with broken/missing logos** (7 brands use an emoji "📱" instead of an HTTP URL):
- zündapp, frans, suzuki, messerschmitt, myers, rover, dacia

**File**: `c:\Users\96650\OneDrive\Desktop\AI_BA_WORKSPACE\tools\ph_common.py` (lines 16-560)

The `BRAND_DATABASE` dict is the upstream source of truth. It contains the same brand entries as brands.json but organized as a Python dict keyed by brand ID. It has ~130 entries (some brands in brands.json were added separately without updating ph_common.py). Categories are identical in structure. Notable: there are duplicate entries for "škoda" (unicode key at line 476 and ASCII "skoda"/"koda" at lines 545-546).

