### 2. Product Categories

**File**: `c:\Users\96650\OneDrive\Desktop\AI_BA_WORKSPACE\data\products.json` (1,412 total products)

**Category distribution**:

| Category | Count |
|----------|-------|
| auto | 700 |
| phone | 640 |
| laptop | 33 |
| smartwatch | 22 |
| tv | 11 |
| camera | 5 |
| tablet | 1 |

**Common product fields** (present on all products):
- `id`, `brand`, `name`, `category`
- `image` (URL), `fallbackImg` (local SVG path)
- `releaseDate` (varied formats: "Released 2026, March 11" or ISO "2025-10-01")
- `basePrice` (number, many are 0)
- `popularity` (integer 40-99), `rating` (float 3.0-5.0), `reviewCount` (integer)
- `review` (AI-generated text)
- `quickSpecs` (object with keys: display, processor, ram, storage, camera, battery)

**Key observations**:
- Most `basePrice` values are 0 (pricing data not populated for most products)
- Non-phone categories (laptop, tv, camera, smartwatch, auto) have sparse quickSpecs -- many fields are empty strings
- The AI reviews for non-phone products often read awkwardly (e.g., "This device appears to be a camera rather than a phone")
- Auto products number 700, nearly matching phones at 640

